{
  "name": "Track AI Edits with Agent",
  "version": "1.0.3",
  "description": "Uses askAgent to track AI-generated edits - only the changed portions",
  "when": {
    "type": "postToolUse",
    "toolTypes": ["write", "fs_write"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "If the file just written is ai-edits.json, do nothing and skip this hook. Otherwise, YOU MUST perform ALL of the following steps - this is MANDATORY, not optional:\n\n1. Determine ABSOLUTE_PATH by combining $(pwd) with the relative file path from the tool output\n2. Find the git repository root (use git rev-parse --show-toplevel)\n3. Set TRACKING_FILE = <git_root>/.attribution/ai-edits.json\n4. Read the current tracking file content (create empty array [] if file doesn't exist)\n5. Parse the JSON and find/create the entry for ABSOLUTE_PATH\n6. Append a new tracking entry with: {file: ABSOLUTE_PATH, lines: {start: startLine, end: endLine}, source: 'ai', content: onlyTheNewOrChangedContent, timestamp: ISO8601, aiTool: 'kiro-ide', aiModel: the AI model name from model_information in system prompt}\n7. Write the updated JSON back to TRACKING_FILE\n\nThe tracking file structure is: [[absolutePath1, [entry1, entry2]], [absolutePath2, [entry3]]]\n\nIMPORTANT: For 'Edit' and 'StrReplace' operations, only include the NEW or CHANGED content in the 'content' field (the replacement text), NOT the entire file. For 'Write' on a new file, include the full content. The 'lines' field should reflect the line range of the change within the file.\n\nNEVER guess paths - always derive them from pwd and the relative path. Ensure .attribution directory exists before writing.\n7. After Updating TRACKING_FILE, check if the git repository root's .gitignore file has entry for .attribution/. If present, skip, otherwise add '.attribution/'\n Do not provide any explanation, just execute the steps silently."
  }
}
